				 Vedanti
																								Lucknow, Oct. 4: The head first, the tongue again  Ram Vilas Vedanti is not done with M. Karunanidhi yet.																								The former BJP MP today again claimed that the Bhagwad Gita says the tongue of anyone who abuses your god should be chopped off.																								Minutes later, not realising the limitations of a man without a tongue, he dared the DMK chief to a debate on Ram. I can give my life to the cause of Ram and Ram setu, he said, renewing his offensive against the Tamil Nadu chief minister on the Sethusamudram ship channel controversy.
